---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  pageHeading="Hardware Selection"
  description="You don't need expensive equipment. Here's what actually works for KC mesh, organized by budget and use case."
>
  <!-- Intro -->
  <section class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
    <h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold leading-tight text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">
      What hardware to buy
    </h2>
    <p class="text-xl text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
      This isn't amateur radio. You don't need thousands of dollars of equipment. $25-50 gets you started. $100-200 buys a complete permanent outdoor setup.
    </p>
    <p class="text-xl text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
      Here's what works, organized by use case and budget.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Device Selection -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Radio devices</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
      <article class="rounded-3xl border-2 border-kc-blue/30 bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-kc-blue/20 dark:bg-sand-900">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">Heltec LoRa32 V3 — Budget Entry</h3>
          <div class="text-xl font-bold text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">$25-30</div>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Testing, learning, indoor use, absolute minimum budget</p>
          <p><strong>Pros:</strong> Cheap, has screen, WiFi capable, proven hardware</p>
          <p><strong>Cons:</strong> No GPS, basic antenna connector, needs external battery for mobile use</p>
          <p><strong>My take:</strong> This is what I started with. Got me on the mesh for under $30. If you're not sure you want to invest yet, start here.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border-2 border-mesh-green/30 bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-mesh-green/20 dark:bg-sand-900">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-mesh-green">LILYGO T-Beam — Mobile/GPS</h3>
          <div class="text-xl font-bold text-mesh-green">$40-50</div>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Mobile use, position tracking, vehicle mounting, hiking/camping</p>
          <p><strong>Pros:</strong> GPS built in, good battery life, 18650 battery support, active community</p>
          <p><strong>Cons:</strong> $15-20 more than basic Heltec, slightly larger form factor</p>
          <p><strong>My take:</strong> This is what I'd buy if starting over. GPS is worth the extra cost for most use cases.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border-2 border-prairie-gold/30 bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-prairie-gold/20 dark:bg-sand-900">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-prairie-gold">RAK WisBlock Meshtastic — Infrastructure</h3>
          <div class="text-xl font-bold text-prairie-gold">$60-80</div>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Router nodes, permanent outdoor deployment, repeater sites</p>
          <p><strong>Pros:</strong> Modular design, excellent build quality, good for weatherproof installations</p>
          <p><strong>Cons:</strong> More expensive, overkill for casual testing</p>
          <p><strong>My take:</strong> If you're deploying backbone infrastructure or hosting a router site, this is the better choice. Worth the investment for permanent installations.</p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 rounded-xl bg-kc-red/10 border border-kc-red/30 p-5 dark:bg-sunset-amber/10 dark:border-sunset-amber/30">
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
        <strong>Where to buy:</strong> Amazon (fast, easy returns), official Meshtastic store, or AliExpress (cheaper, slower). <strong>Make sure you're buying 915 MHz version (US frequency).</strong> EU versions (868 MHz) won't work on KC mesh.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Antennas -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Antennas</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p>
        Stock antennas work. Better antennas dramatically improve range. If you're deploying permanently outdoors, spend the $20-40 on a real antenna.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Stock / Rubber Duck</h3>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p><strong>Cost:</strong> Included ($0-10)</p>
          <p><strong>Gain:</strong> 2-3 dBi</p>
          <p><strong>Range:</strong> 0.5-2 miles typical</p>
          <p><strong>Use:</strong> Testing, indoor, mobile handheld</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Outdoor Omnidirectional</h3>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p><strong>Cost:</strong> $15-40</p>
          <p><strong>Gain:</strong> 5-8 dBi</p>
          <p><strong>Range:</strong> 3-8 miles (with elevation)</p>
          <p><strong>Use:</strong> Residential routers, permanent outdoor nodes</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">High-Gain Collinear</h3>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p><strong>Cost:</strong> $30-60</p>
          <p><strong>Gain:</strong> 8-12 dBi</p>
          <p><strong>Range:</strong> 10+ miles (at tower height)</p>
          <p><strong>Use:</strong> Repeater sites, maximum coverage deployments</p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 rounded-xl bg-mesh-green/10 border border-mesh-green/30 p-5">
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
        <strong>Router 1 setup:</strong> Using 5.8 dBi omnidirectional outdoor antenna (~$25). Gets 5-8 miles from 15-foot elevation. More than adequate for residential router.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Power Solutions -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Power options</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Battery Only (Mobile/Testing)</h3>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p><strong>What:</strong> 18650 battery (1-2 cells) or USB power bank</p>
          <p><strong>Cost:</strong> $10-25</p>
          <p><strong>Runtime:</strong> 12-48 hours depending on device and config</p>
          <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Mobile nodes, testing, temporary deployments</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Small Solar Kit (Residential Router)</h3>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p><strong>What:</strong> 10-20W solar panel + 10Ah LiFePO4 battery + charge controller</p>
          <p><strong>Cost:</strong> $50-100</p>
          <p><strong>Runtime:</strong> Continuous (survives days of clouds)</p>
          <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Residential routers, permanent outdoor nodes</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-ink-600 dark:text-cream-200">This is what Router 1 uses. 10W panel, 10Ah battery. Running for months without issue.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">AC Power (Fixed Indoor/Outdoor)</h3>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p><strong>What:</strong> USB power adapter or weatherproof PSU</p>
          <p><strong>Cost:</strong> $10-30</p>
          <p><strong>Runtime:</strong> Continuous (as long as power available)</p>
          <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Attic installations, tower sites with AC access, indoor routers</p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6">
      <a href="/guides/solar-residential" class="text-base font-medium text-kc-blue hover:text-kc-red dark:text-kc-sky dark:hover:text-sunset-amber">
        Detailed solar setup guide with anti-dogma sizing →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Complete Kits -->
  <section class="mt-12 rounded-3xl border-2 border-kc-blue/30 bg-gradient-to-br from-kc-blue/5 to-kc-sky/10 p-6 sm:p-8 dark:border-kc-sky/20 dark:from-kc-blue/10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Complete kit examples</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border-light bg-surface-200 p-5 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-800">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Beginner: Just Testing (~$35)</h3>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <li>• Heltec V3 device ($25-30)</li>
          <li>• Stock antenna (included)</li>
          <li>• USB power bank you already own ($0)</li>
          <li>• Meshtastic app (free)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border-light bg-surface-200 p-5 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-800">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Mobile/GPS: Vehicle or Hiking (~$75)</h3>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <li>• T-Beam with GPS ($40-50)</li>
          <li>• 18650 batteries x2 ($10-15)</li>
          <li>• Better rubber duck antenna ($10-15)</li>
          <li>• Protective case ($10)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border-light bg-surface-200 p-5 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-800">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Router: Residential Outdoor (~$150)</h3>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <li>• RAK WisBlock or Heltec V3 ($30-70)</li>
          <li>• 5-8 dBi outdoor antenna ($20-30)</li>
          <li>• 10-20W solar panel ($20-30)</li>
          <li>• 10Ah LiFePO4 battery ($25-35)</li>
          <li>• Weatherproof enclosure ($15-20)</li>
          <li>• Mounting hardware (pole/clamps) ($20-30)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Not to Buy -->
  <section class="mt-12 rounded-3xl border-2 border-kc-red/30 bg-gradient-to-br from-kc-red/5 to-sunset-amber/5 p-6 sm:p-8 dark:border-sunset-amber/20 dark:from-kc-red/10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-kc-red dark:text-sunset-amber">What not to buy</h2>
    <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
      <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-kc-red dark:text-sunset-amber">✗</span><span><strong>EU frequency devices (868 MHz)</strong> — Won't work in US. Make sure it's 915 MHz.</span></li>
      <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-kc-red dark:text-sunset-amber">✗</span><span><strong>Non-Meshtastic LoRa boards</strong> — Generic LoRa modules won't run Meshtastic firmware.</span></li>
      <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-kc-red dark:text-sunset-amber">✗</span><span><strong>Massive solar overkill</strong> — You don't need 50W panels and 20Ah batteries for a router. 10W + 10Ah works.</span></li>
      <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-kc-red dark:text-sunset-amber">✗</span><span><strong>Cheap SMA adapters from sketchy vendors</strong> — They fail and introduce loss. Buy from known sellers.</span></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Next Steps -->
  <section class="mt-12 text-center">
    <div class="inline-block rounded-3xl bg-gradient-to-br from-kc-blue to-kc-red p-8 text-cream-50 shadow-card md:p-10">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Hardware ordered?</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-xl text-base opacity-95">
        While you wait for delivery, install the Meshtastic app and read through the setup guide so you're ready to configure as soon as it arrives.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <a
          href="/get-started/join"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-cream-50 px-6 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-kc-blue transition hover:bg-surface-200"
        >
          Setup Guide
        </a>
        <a
          href="/get-started/quick-start"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-cream-50 px-6 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-cream-50 transition hover:bg-cream-50 hover:text-kc-blue"
        >
          Quick Start (Experienced)
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
